# StarCaster — agent rules (shim)

Canonical conventions live in CLAUDE.md files, kept current as the code
changes:

1. Read `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root — non-negotiable invariants
   (generated files, landmines, definition of done).
2. Read the `CLAUDE.md` nearest the files you are editing:
   `components/`, `src/css/`, `routes/`, `public/js/`, `lib/builder-client/`.
3. Architecture, known issues, and roadmap: `docs/FABLE_OVERHAUL_PLAN.md`.

Enforcement is mechanical, not honor-system: a pre-commit hook runs
`scripts/check_conventions.cjs` (stale build artifacts, `public/js/`
freeze, table-header rules). If it blocks you, fix the cause — don't
bypass without stating why.

When you change how something works, update the affected CLAUDE.md in the
same commit. Stale rules are worse than no rules.
